article.headline: Old Dominion 87, DePaul 43
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Arnaud Dahi and Drew Williamson each scored 18 points and Old Dominion turned it on in the second half to beat DePaul 87-43 on Saturday. Williamson was 5-of-8 from beyond the arch, sinking four 3-pointers in the second half. Old Dominion (7-2) rebounded from a slow first half to go 22-for-33 after the break, shooting 57.4 percent for the game. DePaul (5-4) never got anything going, shooting 24.1 percent. Draelon Burns led the Blue Demons with eight points. Old Dominion led 29-22 at halftime, but broke it open early in the second half. Dahi had three consecutive treys to extend the lead to 47-30 with 12:56 remaining. The Monarchs then went on a 27-6 run, fueled by 3-pointers from Williamson, Brian Henderson and Dahi. Old Dominion made 12 of its 23 3-point attempts. Isaiah Hunter and Brian Henderson each had 11 for the Monarchs. Old Dominion outrebounded DePaul 43-31.
